content: I like to keep it simple, so I usually just add some sliced banana and a sprinkle of cinnamon to my oatmeal and yogurt. Sometimes I'll add a few chopped nuts like walnuts or almonds for some crunch. I find that the sweetness from the honey and coconut sugar is enough, so I don't need to add any other sweetener. Speaking of cooking, I've been trying to meal prep more and was wondering if you have any tips on how to store cooked food safely and keep it fresh for a longer period?
